social_posts.post_text: Splash Patience…💦 🤍 and a little Love, Joy & Peace.

While December is typically regarded as “the most wonderful time of the year,” it can also be “the most difficult time of year” for many. The complexities of life can stress us out and overwhelm us, steeling our hope and joy. Meet Dr. Rick Blackmon, a clinical psychologist and the person church leaders, adults and families turn to when they have questions around their own spiritual journeys and how to handle the twists and turns of life. Step into the splash zone and listen to Dr. Blackmon as he shares some of his favorite tools, pieces of advice and words of encouragement for those who need a little extra this holiday season and beyond.

Skip the extra is something we truly believe in here at Skip1. Forego the extra, the boujee, the cherry on top -- instead of splurging on something, give that money instead to Skip1. You won’t miss it and we promise you, it’ll have a huge impact on the children we help feed. 

#skiptember #skip1 #kitchens #foodandwater #families #communities

Skipping something small makes a GIANT difference when everyone does it. It’s at scale that we can have a great impact on the lives of children, their families and the communities we help support. Thank you for Skipping with us this Skiptember!

Today is the last day of Skiptember but you can keep skipping your way right into October. Continue skipping, continue helping us bring food and water projects to those who need it most. Continue sharing your Skip stories and help us make a difference. Thanks again for joining us and skipping with us this month. 

#skiptember #skip1 #kitchens #foodandwater #families #communities

We can’t thank you enough for all your support this past Skiptember. Because of your donations and your willingness to skip it, the children we serve, their families and their communities will have access to meals for many months. Remember, you don’t have to skip something during Skiptember. Skipping something to feed a child in need is a privilege we all get year-round.

We help solve world hunger, one Skip at a time, by building and renovating kitchens within orphanages and schools in impoverished areas. We also support food distribution and feeding programs in places where kitchens can’t be built, and help with clean water and sustainable agricultural initiatives. It’s amazing what can happen when people Skip.
